  "edge_hypothesis": "T3 is a triple-smoothed EMA that produces the lowest-noise moving average available — it filters whipsaws that cause false signals in standard EMAs. When price crosses above/below T3, it captures a smoothed trend change. Supertrend direction gate independently confirms structural trend alignment using ATR-based trailing stops. These are two completely independent smoothing methods (statistical vs structural) that have never been paired. T3 has never been tested as a primary signal despite being available since the indicator library was built. If smooth entries reduce false signals, the dual-confirmation should produce higher win rates at standard R:R ratios. Tests the hypothesis that noise reduction at entry > signal frequency.",
